description.narrative: The USAID Power the Future activity has the overall goal to accelerate the regional transition to high-performing, low-emission, climate-resilient economies. This will be achieved by implementing key intended nationally determined contributions (INDC) commitments through increasing the deployment of renewable energy and energy efficiency in all five Central Asian countries, while improving their ability to meet, track, and develop more ambitious commitments to reduce greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions.
